_:Naeb01b92040a419c851c6f7911de8892 <http://schema.org/itemListElement> _:N28d85d5df4564997935e5fbe80f91f14 <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
_:N5f8b5e1ea89a46dcbc1137ec2ed04552 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Professor Peter Bryant is Chief Executive Officer of the World Nuclear Transport Institute (<abbr title=\"World Nuclear Transport Institute\">WNTI</abbr>), a not-for-profit that represents the global industry on the safe, secure and sustainable transport of radioactive materials.</p>\n\n<p>He has extensive experience in radiation protection and nuclear safety, having served as Director of ESG &amp; Radiation Strategy and previously Head of Environment, Decommissioning &amp; Radiation Safety at Sizewell C / EDF. In these roles he led Environmental Permitting, Funded Decommissioning, Radiation Protection, Radioactive Waste Management and Emergency Planning.</p>\n\n<p>Professor Bryant is a member of the International Commission on Radiological Protection (<abbr title=\"International Commission on Radiological Protection\">ICRP</abbr>) Committee 4 and a recognised authority on radiation protection science. He holds an Honorary Professorship at the University of Liverpool, where he contributes to research and teaching in radiation protection and nuclear policy.</p>\n\n<p>He is also well known for his expertise in stakeholder engagement and risk communication, supporting the <abbr title=\"International Atomic Energy Agency\">IAEA</abbr> in international missions and teaching on its stakeholder engagement school.</p>\n\n<p>Appointed: October 2025<br> \nTerm ends: September 2029</p>\n\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
